    "ideation": "The saluting face is a performance of duty, respect, and sudden discipline. The emotional arc begins with a neutral, perhaps slightly casual state that snaps instantly into a rigid, wide-eyed attention. To simulate the hand physically obscuring part of the face, the right eye undergoes a unique transformation: it narrows significantly as if the brim of a cap or the hand itself is pressing down, while the left eye stays perfectly sharp and open. The mouth becomes a completely flat, serious line to represent 'locked-in' focus. The colors shift from a standard robotic amber to a crisp, ceremonial gold and patriotic navy to ground the expression in its formal context.",
